    "text": "Folks, I’m looking for your help finding my next adventure. Two options which I can offer right now:\n\n🔹 3-6 months projects in the areas of my key expertise, or\n🔹 A long term role with space to grow development skills (preferably Python) which could be done from a different continent in the future—I can elaborate over DM :) Topics closest to my heart: #devtooling / #monitoring / #climate / #education \n\nIn both cases I can offer up to 30hrs/week at this point, starting from September.\n\nHow you can help:\n\n🔹 Know someone who could use my help? Please point them to me.\n🔹 You could use my help? Let’s chat!\n🔹 We've worked together and you had a good experience? Consider writing a LI reference.\n🔹 Share this message.\n🔹 None of the above, but you still want to say hi? My DMs are always open :)\n\nThank you all. As you can see, my drawing skills will probably not help me pay rent anytime soon :D\n\nCheers,\nDaria\n\n-----\n\nWith over 5 years of hands-on experience in software engineering, my primary focus has been on Site Reliability Engineering (SRE). Throughout my career, I've helped run production systems for diverse organizations, from fast-growing startups to a major public cloud provider. As an operational generalist, I've successfully tackled various aspects, including CI/CD pipelines, automation, infrastructure, monitoring, and alerting, among other critical areas. My archetype would be Organizer.\n\nNot limited to the operational side, I’ve contributed to product development (Node.js), allowing me to empathize with my colleagues on the dev side. My favorite projects to date include introducing Incident Response programs that turn chaos into calm work. I also built an on-call training program that went upstream in an engineering organization of a few thousand people.\n\nIn my past life, before switching to engineering, I worked on the business side. From that, I bring years of experience with people in communication, sales, support, and leadership roles. When I need a break from computers I organize things with people (Python conferences, meetups.)\n\n🔹 Experienced in software engineering with a focus on SRE\n🔹 Skilled in CI/CD pipelines, automation, infrastructure, monitoring, and alerting\n🔹 Hands-on experience implementing SLOs and SLIs\n🔹 Empathetic and with experience on the business side\n🔹 Experienced in event management (conferences, meetups)\n🔹 Enthusiastic about introducing transformative Incident Response programs\n🔹 Successful in implementing impactful on-call training initiatives\n\nIf you’re looking for someone to help with incident response, on-calls, and production systems in general—let’s chat and explore how I can contribute: hello@dariagrudzien.com\n\n#sre #softwareengineering #incidentresponse #oncall #monitoring #slo #sli #python #iac #cicdpipelines",
